main event: An object that appeared round and luminous was observed hovering in the sky on July 20, 1961, moving erratically before disappearing.
interesting points: The length of the observation was 40-45 minutes., Witnesses did not feel the object was an aircraft., There was an inability to explain the nature or origin of the object., The sighting was categorized as Unidentified., The report comes from a Project Blue Book record card.
sighted object: round and luminous object in the sky
witness description: witnesses included the ship's navigator and three others on the bridge.
